cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with privacy against an adversary that tries to detect the underlying privacy-sensitive data distribution. This involves information theory (cs.IT) as the privacy leakage is measured by the probability of error of the binary hypothesis test carried out by the adversary. The paper also deals with adversarial attacks and defenses, which falls under computer security (cs.CR). The management unit (MU) is allowed to manipulate the original data sequence in an online fashion, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions Bayesian tests, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
